<TITLE> Two killed in shootout with RAB </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 7 (bdnews24.com)  Two suspected criminals were killed in gunfight with RAB in Dhaka and Pabna early on Wednesday. 28-year old Hedayetullah Julhas aka Julu was killed in the capital's Hajaribagh area while 30-year old Mokhter Hossain was killed in Pabna sadar upazila. RAB-2 operation officer Talebur Rahman told bdnews24.com that being tipped off that a group of criminals had gathered beside Ali CNG Filling Station near Hajaribagh dam, the elite force team went to the scene. Sensing their arrival, the criminals fired shots forcing the elite force to fire back, Rahman said. At one stage, the criminals fled the scene leaving Julu with bullet wounds, he said. Julu was rushed to Dhaka Medical College Hospital where the duty doctors declared him dead. RAB recovered one pistol from the scene. Julu, a close associate of top criminal Emon, faced seven cases, the RAB official said. Meanwhile, RAB-12 Pabna camp deputy commander flight lieutenant Ahmed Faisal said they had gone to Kachhipara of Chartara union at around 1:15am on a tip-off that the some operatives of extremist Sarbahara Party were holding a secret meeting there. As the criminals sensed the presence of law enforcers they opened fire which the elite force retaliated, he said. During the 30-minuite shootout Mokhter died on the spot, the official said. RAB recovered one local-made pistol, three rounds of ammunition and one big dagger from the scene. Mokhter, a regional leader of Sarbahara Party, faced at least eight cases including three murder cases, Faisal said. bdn
